# --- COMMIT END ---
# Type can be:
#    feat     (new feature for the user)
#    fix      (bug fix for the user)
#    docs     (changes to documentation)
#    style    (formatting, missing semi colons, etc; no code change)
#    refactor (refactoring production code)
#    test     (adding missing tests, refactoring tests; no production code change)
#    chore    (updating build tasks, package manager configs, etc; no production code change)
#
# Scope can be:
#    component name, file name, or area affected
#    Examples: dashboard, photos, auth, api, docs
#
# Subject should:
#    - use imperative, present tense: "change" not "changed" nor "changes"
#    - don't capitalize first letter
#    - no dot (.) at the end
#
# Body should:
#    - explain WHAT and WHY (not HOW - code shows that)
#    - include motivation for the change
#    - contrast with previous behavior
#
# Footer should:
#    - reference issues, PRs, breaking changes
#    - use "Fixes #123" for GitHub to auto-close issues
#    - note breaking changes with "BREAKING CHANGE:"
#
# Example good commits:
#    feat(photos): add filtering by date range
#    fix(auth): resolve login redirect loop
#    docs(readme): update installation instructions
#    refactor(dashboard): extract stats calculation to utility
#    chore(deps): upgrade Next.js to v16.0.2
